%N A019762 Decimal expansion of 2*e.
%C A019762 Simple continued fraction is A081750. - _Michael Somos_, May 07 2012
%C A019762 2*e - 3 = 2.436563... is the expected number of real numbers that are independently and uniformly selected at random from the interval (0, 1) until they are no longer monotonically increasing or monotonically decreasing (Shultz and Leonard, 1989). - _Amiram Eldar_, Jun 09 2026
%H A019762 Ivan Panchenko, <a href="/A019762/b019762.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000</a>
%H A019762 Harris S. Shultz and Bill Leonard, <a href="https://www.jstor.org/stable/2689770">Unexpected Occurrences of the Number e</a>, Mathematics Magazine, Vol. 62, No. 4 (1989), pp. 269-271.
%H A019762 <a href="/index/Tra#transcendental">Index entries for transcendental numbers</a>.
%F A019762 Equals Sum_{n>=1} n^2/n!. - _Arkadiusz Wesolowski_, Mar 11 2013
%F A019762 From _Richard R. Forberg_, Dec 23 2014: (Start)
%F A019762 Equals lim_{x->1} (x*e^x - e)/(x-1).
%F A019762 Equals Sum_{n>=0} Sum_{k=0..n} 1/n!. (End)
%F A019762 Equals 1 + (2/1) + (3/2/1) + (4/3/2/1) + (5/4/3/2/1) + (6/5/4/3/2/1) + ... . - _Davide Rotondo_, Apr 07 2024
%e A019762 5.43656365691809047072057494270532499551449418739991914993...
